  "notes": "Standard Urdu (Pakistan national language, Indian Muslim register). Phonologically near-identical to Hindi but with additional phonemes from Persian/Arabic loans: /q x ɣ f z/. Written right-to-left in Nastaliq (a form of Perso-Arabic script). Four-way laryngeal contrast: plain/aspirated × voiced/voiceless. Retroflex series: /ʈ ɖ ɽ/ graphically distinct from dentals.",
